    "How does students' AI interaction profiles associate with students' performance within each intervention?",
    "Early implementations of chatbots in education, such as the use of rule-based systems, were primarily focused on providing automated responses to common queries.",
    "Studies demonstrated that these chatbots could reduce the workload of educators by handling routine questions, thereby allowing instructors to focus on more complex student needs (Alemdag, 2023).",
    "However, the limitations of rule-based systems, particularly their inability to handle nuanced or unexpected questions, constrained their effectiveness (Khennouche et al., 2024; Wu & Yu, 2024).",
    "On the other hand, the advent of new generation chatbots, based on Generative Pre-trained Transformer (GPT) architecture and LLMs, has significantly advanced their capabilities."
  ],
